README.md
Yuno QA Automation Assessment

Overview
This repository contains a QA Automation framework built using Python + Behave (BDD) to validate Yuno payment orchestration APIs.
It covers purchase, refund, authorization, capture, cancel, and verify payment flows.

Tech Stack
Python 3.x
Behave (BDD)

Project Structure

features/
 ├─ purchase.feature
 ├─ refund.feature
 ├─ authorization.feature
 ├─ cancel.feature
 └─ verify.feature
features/steps/
 └─ common_steps.py
utils/
 ├─ api_client.py
 └─ payload_builder.py

Test Coverage
Purchase (Sanity & Negative)
Refund
Authorization → Capture
Authorization → Cancel
Verify Payment
Tags: @sanity, @regression, @integration

Setup & Run
pip install -r requirements.txt
python -m behave


Run by tag:
python -m behave --tags=@sanity

Notes
API responses are mocked
workflow is set to DIRECT
Focus is on test design & coverage

Documentation
Detailed test cases are available in Test_Case_Documentation.md

Run python -m behave to execute all tests successfully.